Merkel Gets a Surprise Challenger
BERLIN—Germany's opposition Social Democrats tapped former Finance Minister Peer Steinbrück to challenge Angela Merkel in next year's general election, an unexpected move that sets the stage for a battle over the country's political center and a campaign focused on how to fix the euro zone.
